      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your concern about the cost, but your health is the top priority. Even if you don't have a fever, the location and nature of your pain could still indicate appendicitis, which is a medical emergency. Taking ibuprofen and codeine together can increase the risk of serious side effects, including overdose. I strongly recommend you seek medical attention immediately. It's better to be safe and have it checked out than to risk your health further. There are often emergency rooms that offer sliding scale fees based on income, or you could call your local urgent care clinic for a more affordable option. Please prioritize your health.",
